		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Social capital</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Social capital</b> is a concept developed in <a href="/wiki/Sociology" title="Sociology">sociology</a> and also used in business, <a href="/wiki/Capital_(economics)" title="Capital (economics)">economics</a>, <a href="/wiki/Organizational_behaviour" title="Organizational behaviour" class="mw-redirect">organizational behaviour</a>, <a href="/wiki/Political_science" title="Political science">political science</a>, <a href="/wiki/Public_health" title="Public health">public health</a> and natural resources management that refers to connections within and between <a href="/wiki/Social_network" title="Social network">social networks</a> as well as connections among individuals. Though there are a variety of related definitions, which have been described as "<i>something of a cure-all</i>"<sup id="cite_ref-Portes_1998_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Portes_1998-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> for the problems of modern <a href="/wiki/Society" title="Society">society</a>, they tend to share the core idea "that <a href="/wiki/Social_network" title="Social network">social networks</a> have <a href="/wiki/Value_theory" title="Value theory">value</a>. Just as a screwdriver (<a href="/wiki/Physical_capital" title="Physical capital">physical capital</a>) or a college education (<a href="/wiki/Human_capital" title="Human capital">human capital</a>) can increase productivity (both individual and collective), so do social contacts affect the productivity of individuals and groups".<sup id="cite_ref-Putnam_2000_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Putnam_2000-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
